<h1>Privacy notice</h1>
<p><small>GDPR Article 13 disclosure for visitors to <code>{{ ja4proxy_domain }}</code>.
Last updated on first deployment of this host.</small></p>

<p>This site is a <strong>research honeypot</strong>. It looks like a
web form but is operated for the sole purpose of collecting TLS
fingerprints from automated scanners and abuse traffic. The operator
does not solicit, want, or store legitimate human data submitted to
this host.</p>

<h2>Controller</h2>
<p>The data controller for any processing described on this page is
the operator of <code>{{ ja4proxy_domain }}</code>. Contact:
<code>privacy@{{ ja4proxy_domain }}</code>. Abuse reports:
<code>abuse@{{ ja4proxy_domain }}</code>.</p>

<h2>Lawful basis</h2>
<p>Processing is carried out under <strong>GDPR Article 6(1)(f) —
legitimate interests</strong>. The legitimate interest is
information-security research into attacker TLS fingerprints and
abusive traffic patterns. A balancing assessment has concluded that
this interest is not overridden by the rights of data subjects
because (a) the service is a decoy and does not hold accounts, (b)
form submissions are discarded rather than retained, and (c)
identifiers collected are IP-level metadata, not content.</p>

<h2>Purposes</h2>
<ul>
<li>Generate and publish anonymised TLS-fingerprint datasets for the
research community.</li>
<li>Detect, block, and report abusive traffic at the network edge.</li>
<li>Operate the service itself (rate limiting, banning, diagnostics).</li>
</ul>

<h2>Categories of data</h2>
<ul>
<li>IP addresses of incoming connections, plus TCP/TLS handshake
metadata (JA4 fingerprints, cipher suites, ALPN).</li>
<li>HTTP request metadata (method, path, User-Agent, referrer).</li>
<li>Coarse geolocation and ASN derived from the IP via MaxMind GeoLite2.</li>
<li><strong>No content from form fields is stored.</strong> Submissions
are discarded before they touch persistent storage.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Retention</h2>
<p>Observability data is retained for
<strong>{{ ja4proxy_loki_retention_days }} days</strong> (logs) and
<strong>{{ ja4proxy_prometheus_retention_days }} days</strong> (metrics),
after which it is deleted by automatic retention policies. Short-lived
ban entries expire from Redis within minutes. Evidence tarballs
produced in response to an incident are retained only as long as the
investigation requires and are then shredded.</p>

<h2>Recipients</h2>
<p>Data is not sold or shared with advertising networks. Anonymised
aggregates may be shared with the research community or with upstream
network providers responding to an abuse report. Law-enforcement
disclosures are made only in response to a valid legal order.</p>

<h2>International transfers</h2>
<p>The service is hosted in the EU. No personal data is intentionally
transferred outside the EEA. GeoIP lookups are performed locally
against an on-host database — no third-party API call is made for
that enrichment.</p>

<h2>Your rights</h2>
<p>Under the GDPR you have the right to <strong>access, rectification,
erasure, restriction, objection, and portability</strong> regarding
your personal data, and the right to lodge a complaint with a
supervisory authority. Because this host does not hold accounts, an
access or erasure request must include the IP address and approximate
timestamp so we can locate the relevant records. Send requests to
<code>privacy@{{ ja4proxy_domain }}</code>; we will respond within
30 days.</p>

<h2>Automated decision-making</h2>
<p>Automated rate-limiting and banning decisions are made at the edge
based on TLS-fingerprint reputation. These decisions have no legal
or similarly significant effect on natural persons — they only
throttle or reject traffic to this decoy host.</p>

<h2>Contact</h2>
<p>Privacy questions: <code>privacy@{{ ja4proxy_domain }}</code><br>
Abuse reports: <code>abuse@{{ ja4proxy_domain }}</code><br>
Security disclosures: see <a href="/.well-known/security.txt">security.txt</a>.</p>

</body>
